solution.p:
        	Since the period of a function is related to B, the stretch/compression factor, we can use the relationship P = 2\pi/B to solve for B. Substituting 5 in for P, we get

        	 5 \amp= \frac{2\pi}{B} 

        	 B \cdot 5 \amp= 2\pi 

        	 B \amp= \frac{2\pi}{5} 

			For now, we can assume that the B value is positive, which gives us
			 B = \frac{2\pi}{5}

Since we know the period is 4, we can use the relationship P = 2\pi/B to solve for B. Substituting 4 in for P, we get

 4 \amp= \frac{2\pi}{B} 

 B \cdot 4 \amp= 2\pi 

 B \amp= \frac{2\pi}{4} 

 B \amp= \frac{\pi}{2}
